markets.title: Will the next government funding bill be a 'clean CR'?
markets.rules_primary: If the next government funding bill that becomes law is a ‘clean continuing resolution’ before Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: A clean continuing resolution is a funding measure that temporarily extends current government spending at the previous fiscal year’s levels for a specified period, without incorporating any additional policy provisions, earmarks, or modifications to agency operations.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the event occurs.
